    "body" : "<p>For those using Cobertura and only have the Coverage Session View like I do,just try closing Eclipse and starting it up again. This got rid of the highlighting for me.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2095034,
      "reputation" : 193,
      "user_id" : 1864014,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 40,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5f2910dc7fc07b54add7b827e527d2d7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Dan Hankins",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1864014/dan-hankins"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 18,
    "last_activity_date" : 1354210410,
    "creation_date" : 1354210410,
    "answer_id" : 13631439,
    "question_id" : 6112561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I found a workaround over on GitHub: <a href=\"https://github.com/jmhofer/eCobertura/issues/8\">https://github.com/jmhofer/eCobertura/issues/8</a></p>\n\n<p>For those who don't want to click the link, here's the text of the comment:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Good workaround:\n  Create a run configuration with a filter, that excludes everything (\"*\") and let it run just a single test. Name it \"Undo coverage\".</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>I did this and it worked quite well in Eclipse Juno.</p>\n\n<p>Credit for this goes to UsulSK.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5118754,
      "reputation" : 71,
      "user_id" : 4103063,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5973ed781568aadac279044e84673831?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "asdf",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4103063/asdf"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1412265350,
    "creation_date" : 1412265350,
    "answer_id" : 26164704,
    "question_id" : 6112561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Added shortcut Ctrl+Shift+X C to Keybindings (Window -> Preferences -> filter for Keys) when 'Editing Java Source' for 'Remove Active Session'.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7206857,
      "reputation" : 101,
      "user_id" : 5502210,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9657dc2991795379ece7ca306fb5f5ae?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Sandeep Singh",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5502210/sandeep-singh"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1446111810,
    "creation_date" : 1446111810,
    "answer_id" : 33410693,
    "question_id" : 6112561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you remove the coverage session, also the coverage coloring will disappear. For this, hit Remove Session or Remove All Sessions in the Coverage view's toolbar.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://eclemma.org/faq.html\">http://eclemma.org/faq.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6518700,
      "reputation" : 41,
      "user_id" : 5043590,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-iJdYSIHL9ww/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAA9E/RAN9GDQfB3Y/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Sachin Nikam",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5043590/sachin-nikam"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1511158758,
    "creation_date" : 1511158758,
    "answer_id" : 47386062,
    "question_id" : 6112561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you would like to remove active session/project/folder then you can follow</p>\n\n<p>Click the \"Remove Active Session\" button in the toolbar of the \"Coverage\" view.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 10633649,
      "reputation" : 656,
      "user_id" : 7830966,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/UNkuK.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Satya",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7830966/satya"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1530510572,
    "last_edit_date" : 1530510572,
    "creation_date" : 1526434120,
    "answer_id" : 50361220,
    "question_id" : 6112561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Close the IDE and open it again. This works if you did not use any code coverage tools and have just clicked the basic \"Coverage\" icon in the IDE. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9862974,
      "reputation" : 400,
      "user_id" : 7305307,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/aOkVz.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Yash Bansal",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7305307/yash-bansal"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1537982271,
    "creation_date" : 1537982271,
    "answer_id" : 52523052,
    "question_id" : 6112561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I have used the Open Clover Tool for the code coverage, I have also been searching this for a long time. \nIts pretty straightforward, in the Coverage Explorer tab, you can find three square buttons which says the code lines you wanted to display, click on hide the coverage square box and its gone. Last button in the image below:\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Xvrnj.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Xvrnj.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2843520,
      "reputation" : 2752,
      "user_id" : 2442565,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 66,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a3a4826b956dc4fde4bf77a736ce607a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Divyanshu Jimmy",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2442565/divyanshu-jimmy"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 71,
    "last_activity_date" : 1591193102,
    "last_edit_date" : 1591193102,
    "creation_date" : 1568945762,
    "answer_id" : 58020941,
    "question_id" : 6112561,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>For people who are not able to find the coverage view , follow these steps :</strong></p>\n\n<p>Go to Windows Menu bar > Show View > Other > Type coverage and open it.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/nJYTy.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/nJYTy.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Click on Coverage.</strong></p>\n\n<p>To clear highlightings, click on <strong>X or XX</strong> icon as per convenience.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/UY01W.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/UY01W.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
